uter to randomly select a second mode transmission resource from the set of resources associated with the second discovery mode; and program code executable by the computer for causing the computer to transmit the discovery signal using the randomly selected second mode transmission resource. 30. The non-transitory computer-readable medium of claim 27, wherein the first mobility state corresponds to one of: a static mobility state and a transient mobility state. 31. The non-transitory computer-readable medium of claim 27, wherein the first mobility state corresponds to the static mobility state, and wherein the program code executable by the computer for causing the computer to select the transmission resource includes: program code executable by the computer for causing the computer to select a reserved transmission resource, wherein the reserved transmission resource is reserved for the wireless device. 32. The non-transitory computer-readable medium of claim 31, further including: program code executable by the computer for causing the computer to perform an additional contention resolution on the reserved transmission resource after expiration of a first time from the performing the contention resolution; and program code executable by the computer for causing the computer to select a new transmission resource from the set of resources for execution of the program code executable by the computer for causing the computer to transmit only in response to the additional contention resolution being unsuccessful. 33. The non-transitory computer-readable medium of claim 27, wherein the first mobility state corresponds to the transient mobility state, and wherein the program code executable by the computer for causing the computer to select the transmission resource includes: program code executable by the computer for causing the computer to randomly select the transmission resource from the set of resources. 34. The non-transitory computer-readable medium of claim 33,